race.comment: RONNY BEE (5) made a big impression in his SA debut, exploding down the outside and just missing the leading pair. He'll have taken plenty of benefit from that run and should be able to settle a touch closer this time. Expect him to stalk the speed and be very strong late. OUT OF SQUARE (1) was a barnstorming winner fresh but has since struggled against tougher Victorian opposition. Much better placed back at this level and gets a handy 2kg claim. She has to be considered. TRULY ELSA (9) is going along nicely and only needs to hold her form to make her presence felt. MAJOR RUMBLE (8) got the bob at Murray Bridge last start but meets RONNY BEE 2kg worse. He has more to offer but the draw will test him.
